column1: I have plenty of icons for you today!

This means that even though I will be making a bunch of icons, I won't be able to post them at regular intervals.  See you when I can, hopefully bearing a whole bunch of icons!  :)

event,"Over at <lj user=""cap_it"">, some people had requested Robin Hood, the best movie on Earth, so I capped it all. event,"Hello all!  Hope everyone is having a wonderful Halloween!  I'm unfortunately stuck at work, but I went out last night so it's all goooood.

Anyway, I've noticed a disturbing rise of people using my icons WITHOUT crediting me. It gets a tad old. I found this great tutorial on that teaches people how to credit using the comment field. This wonderful tutorial was made by , so all credit, good karma and cyber treats go to her. Anyway, please check it out and please always credit. It just makes life so much easier for everyone involved!

event,"Alright, I have a ton of icons to post, so here's the first batch.  Remember the rules about taking my icons, por favor
This post has all my Into the Woods icons.  All the caps were taken from the OBC DVD.   If you would like to customize one of the textless ones, feel free, just tell me your idea first.  Thankies!

No one really reads this journal anyway, so this isn't a huge deal, but I won't be able to update for quite a while.  I'm going home for the summer and I'm not able to get my computer, which has all my icons and icon making stuff on it, to connect to the internet.  I may be able to use my mom's computer to post some stuff, but that isn't very likely.  Soooo....there will be very few, if any, updates for the next 3 months.  I will be working on icons though, so expect a huge update come the end of September.  Happy summer, y'all!!!!!"
